\begin{verbatim}
Theorem: Forall g |- C, exists unique C* = CANON(g, C) such that
    (1) g |-* C*
    (2) g |-  C -->> C*

Proof: By induction on C

Case C = |hole|:
    return C* = C

Case C = ... C' ...:

    C'* = CANON(g, C')

        As g |- C we have g |- C'
        by IH
            (1') g |-* C'*
            (2') g |-  C' -->> C'*

    C*  = ... C'* ...

        From (1') and def of |-* we get

            g |-* ... C'* ...  i.e.  (1)

        Using the context  CC = ... hole ... (such that g . CC = g) (2') is

            g . CC |-  C' -->> C'*

        Hence, from [exch]

            g |- ... C'... -->> ... C'* ...     i.e. (2)

Case C = x = y; C':

    C'' = subst(C', x, y)

        x=y; C' -->> x=y; C''

        As g |- x=y; C'   by [lem:steps-under] we have

            g |- x=y; C' -->> g |- x=y; C''  (a)

        As no free x in C''

            g + [x => y] |- C''              (b)

    C'* = CANON(g, C'')

        By IH we get

             (1') g + [x=>y] |-* C'*
             (2') g + [x=>y] |-  C'' -->> C'*

    return C* = x = y; C'*

        By (1') we get

            (1) g |-* C*

        By (1') + [exchange]

            (2'') g |- x=y;C'' -->> x=y;C'*

        Combining with (a) and [under-trans] we get

            (2) g |- x = y; C' -->> x = y; C'*
QED.

